abstract: Google announced that it is leading an industry alliance to transform mobile phones into powerful computers.
snippet: Google announced that it is leading an industry alliance to transform mobile phones into powerful computers.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO, Nov. 5 — Google took its long-awaited plunge into the wireless world today, announcing that it is leading a broad industry alliance to transform mobile phones into powerful mobile computers that could accelerate the convergence of computing and communications.

abstract: Time Warner‘s AOL unit plans to pay $300 million for an Israeli advertising start-up, Quigo, in a move to compete better with Google and Yahoo, an Israeli newspaper report said.
lead_paragraph: Time Warner‘s AOL unit plans to pay $300 million for an Israeli advertising start-up, Quigo, in a move to compete better with Google and Yahoo, an Israeli newspaper report said.

headline.main: AOL to Buy Israeli Start-Up, Report Says

abstract: Google said it wasn’t announcing its own cellphone model. Yet. But it did say it planned to cut deals with cellphone carriers to share cellphone advertising revenue.
snippet: Google said it wasn’t announcing its own cellphone model. Yet. But it did say it planned to cut deals with cellphone carriers to share cellphone advertising revenue.

abstract: With Google’s introduction of a cellphone operating system, it adds another front of competition with Apple, even though Eric Schmidt, Google’s chief executive, serves on Apple’s board.
snippet: With Google’s introduction of a cellphone operating system, it adds another front of competition with Apple, even though Eric Schmidt, Google’s chief executive, serves on Apple’s board.
lead_paragraph: On the Google conference call, a reporter asked about another potential reason that Google may want to soft-pedal a possible GPhone: Eric Schmidt serves on Apple’s board of directors.
